
[1]reasonably

   RE'ASONABLY, adv.

   1. In a manner or degree agreeable to reason; in consistency with
   reason. We may reasonably suppose self interest to be the governing
   principle of men.

   2. Moderately; in a moderate degree; not fully; in a degree reaching to
   mediocrity.

   If we can be industry make our deaf and dumb persons reasonably perfect
   in the language -
     __________________________________________________________________

